# *flutter\_content* package

## Introduction

**your flutter widgets visually editable with a devtools-like editor ui**  
With the *flutter\_content* package, you can make parts, or all of your flutter pages, editable visually or declaratively. These editable widget models, we call **snippet**s, get stored in your Firestore database.

**changes are versioned**  
Changes to a snippet are versioned, and you control which version is being edited, and which version is currently being published; i.e. a signed-in editor user will see the editing version, whereas a sign-out user will see the published version.

**Publish new snippet versions without redeploying**  
Your app can be updated in real-time without needing to redeploy, because your snippets in firestore are used to build actual flutter widgets in real-time.

##  API

The *flutter\_content* package allows you to build serialisable models of flutter widgets (we refer to these widget models as **Snippet**s). They get stored in your firestore database.

A **Snippet** is a **tree** of **SNode**s. The *flutter\_content* package defines a hierarchy of dart serialisable classes derived from **SNode**, each modelling a flutter widget (properties and tree structure):

![][image1]Notice, in the diagram above, that even many 3rd party flutter widgets, like those on pub.dev, are modelled by this hierarchy, so can be included in your **Snippets**.

A **Snippet** can be created:

* in your dart source code  
* visually by your signed-in users (editors): The package provides a devtools-like editing user-interface, which can be rendered to your users, who can then edit properties, and manipulate the structure of the tree.

The *flutter\_content* package defines many classes, the most important of which are the following…

* **FlutterContentApp** \- wraps your app: you supply your package configuration, such as your firebase options file, and optionally a RoutingConfig (we use Go\_Router’s, url-based API for navigating between different pages).

* **SNode** \- models a specific flutter widget: its properties, and if it is composed of other widgets, its tree structure  
    
* **SnippetBuilder** \- renders a **Snippet** by recursively calling the build() method of all **SNode**s in its tree; i.e. it generates a real flutter widget.

* **EditablePage** \- wraps your page widget (e.g. a Scaffold), adding either a pencil icon button for the user to sign in as an editor, or if signed-in, with a ‘more’ menu that will contain a sign-out button.

  When an editor is signed in, the ‘more’ menu will also show a link for each page route, including routes that have been dynamically created by editors. (Dynamic pages are explained later).

*  **EditablePageRoute** \- if you are supplying a RoutingConfig to **FlutterContentApp**, this class allows you to specify routes that will be editable pages.
